        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "o-list-item",
        "text": "Appeal to Authority: Naturally enough, arguments from authority often quote experts as a premise. However, it is possible to quote even legitimate experts out of context so as to misrepresent their opinions, which is a form of misleading appeal to authority.",
